<subSubSection id="C37565586427FF8FFF1AF3BC4A47C0A5" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD036D36427FF8FFF1AF3BC485DC047" blockId="23.[189,303,1528,1554]" box="[189,303,1528,1554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<heading id="D09881BF6427FF8FFF1AF3BC485DC047" bold="true" box="[189,303,1528,1554]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16427FF8FFF1AF3BC485DC047" bold="true" box="[189,303,1528,1554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036D36427FF8FFF1AF0624A47C0A5" blockId="23.[188,1399,1574,1777]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506427FF8FFF1AF06248E6C014" box="[189,404,1574,1601]" class="Ostracoda" family="Paraparchitidae" genus="Paraparchites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leiocopa" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16427FF8FFF1AF0624816C015" box="[189,356,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Paraparchites</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFE6DF0634BA8C014" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[458,730,1575,1601]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong (2019)</bibRefCitation>
from the Famennian, late Devonian, of Blue Snake section, 
<collectingRegion id="49ABF8316427FF8FFE83F00E48FEC031" box="[292,396,1610,1636]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, South 
<collectingCountry id="F37876436427FF8FFE48F00E4B47C031" box="[495,565,1610,1636]" name="China" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFDEDF00E4A31C031" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[586,835,1610,1636]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong 2019</bibRefCitation>
) does not belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506427FF8FFB77F00E48A7C0D2" authority="Ulrich &amp; Bassler 1906" authorityName="Ulrich &amp; Bassler" authorityYear="1906" class="Ostracoda" family="Paraparchitidae" genus="Paraparchites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leiocopa" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16427FF8FFB77F00E4C05C031" box="[1232,1399,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Paraparchites</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFF1AF02948A7C0D2" author="Ulrich E. O. &amp; Bassler R. S." box="[189,469,1645,1671]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="149 - 164" refId="ref33559" refString="Ulrich E. O. &amp; Bassler R. S. 1906. New American Palaeozoic Ostracoda. Notes and descriptions of the Upper Carboniferous genera and species. United States National Museum Paper 30: 149 - 164. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.30 - 1446.149" type="journal article" year="1906">Ulrich &amp; Bassler 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as indicated by the postero-dorsal spine on the illustrated right valve. The specimen shown in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFE17F0D44BC1C0FF" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[432,691,1680,1706]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong (2019)</bibRefCitation>
is only questionably attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506427FF8FFBFEF0D448BBC098" authority="Crasquin-Soleau, 1988" authorityName="Crasquin-Soleau" authorityYear="1988" class="Ostracoda" genus="Shishaella" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastierenesis">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16427FF8FFBFEF0D44C04C0FF" box="[1113,1398,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Shishaella hastierenesis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFF1AF0F748BBC098" author="Crasquin-Soleau S." box="[189,457,1715,1741]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="309 - 318" refId="ref28044" refString="Crasquin-Soleau S. 1988. Ostracodes tournaisiens du Massif de la Tombe (Synclinorium de Namur - Belgique). Annales de la Societe geologique de Belgique 110: 309 - 318." type="journal article" year="1988">Crasquin-Soleau, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because the occurrence of a postero-dorsal spine at left valve, which would point to the genus 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16427FF8FFEF5F09248CDC0A5" box="[338,447,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Shivaella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226427FF8FFE60F0924B3DC0A4" author="Sohn I. G." box="[455,591,1750,1777]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref33062" refString="Sohn I. G. 1971. New Late Mississippian Ostracode genera and species from Northern Alaska. A review of the Paraparchitacea. United States Geological Survey Professional Paper 711 A: 1 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.3133 / pp 711 a." type="journal article" year="1971">Sohn, 1971</bibRefCitation>
, cannot be verified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
